                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The blasphemer attempts a @Check[religion|dc:15] check to attempt to cast the 1st-rank spell their deity grants to clerics (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Phantom Pain] for Zon-Kuthon). The spell must take 1, 2, or 3 actions to Cast. The blasphemer can use twisted faith to roll @Check[deception|dc:15] instead if they have a witness, as normal.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The blasphemer successfully Casts the Spell, then is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stunned] with a value equal to the number of actions the spell takes – 1.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> As critical success, plus the blasphemer takes @Damage[1d6[mental]] damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The blasphemer fails to Cast the Spell and takes @Damage[1d6[mental]] damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The blasphemer fails to Cast the Spell, takes @Damage[2d6[mental]] damage, and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stunned]{Stunned 1}.</p>"
